&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About AssetWatch&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AssetWatch helps industrial teams monitor the health of critical equipment through connected hardware, sensing, analytics, and condition monitoring workflows. Our hardware products include battery-powered vibration sensors, edge hubs, wireless communication systems, wired networking interfaces, and factory/test infrastructure that must operate reliably and securely in demanding industrial environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Firmware Engineer to help design, build, test, release, and sustain the firmware that powers our connected hardware platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Firmware Engineer at AssetWatch, you will work on production firmware for industrial IoT devices, including vibration sensors, BLE-enabled devices, edge hubs, diagnostics, firmware updates, wired and wireless networking, Wi-Fi communication, cybersecurity-sensitive firmware protocols, and manufacturing/test workflows. You will collaborate closely with hardware engineering, test engineering, backend/cloud teams, product, support, cybersecurity stakeholders, and manufacturing partners to deliver reliable and secure connected products from prototype through production ramp and field support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who enjoys hands-on embedded development, real hardware debugging, wireless and wired communication, production-quality release discipline, secure firmware design, and cross-functional problem solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Develop and maintain embedded firmware for AssetWatch sensors, hubs, BLE modules, and related hardware systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Design, implement, and debug firmware features for sensor communication, diagnostics, scheduling, data collection, configuration, and firmware updates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Work with BLE communication paths between hubs and battery-powered sensors, including scanning, connection handling, command/response flows, diagnostics, and update behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Develop and debug firmware features involving Wi-Fi communication, wired Ethernet, cellular connectivity, TCP/IP networking, MQTT communication, device diagnostics, and edge-to-cloud data paths.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Support wired and wireless networking behavior across hubs and connected devices, including connectivity state, provisioning, configuration, reconnection behavior, signal quality, network diagnostics, and failure recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Implement and review firmware cybersecurity features and protocols, including secure communication, device identity, authentication, authorization, encrypted transport, credential handling, signed firmware, secure update flows, and protection of device interfaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Support embedded Linux or ed

