&lt;p&gt;AssetWatch is seeking a Senior Tax Manager to establish and lead the company&#39;s tax and compliance function as we continue to scale globally. This is a newly created role, built to own tax and compliance as a dedicated internal capability that was previously managed alongside other accounting responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The company currently operates in the United States and Canada, is actively expanding its presence in Mexico, and is preparing for future growth in the United Kingdom and European markets. This role will serve as the primary internal owner of tax and compliance activities, partnering closely with Accounting leadership and external advisors to ensure compliance, mitigate risk, and support international growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting directly to the VP, Accounting, this is an individual contributor role with access to accounting team support for administrative tasks; team expansion will be evaluated as the function matures and the company continues to grow. You&#39;ll work closely with established external advisors, including BDO and other international tax and legal partners, so you won&#39;t be expected to be a solo expert across every jurisdiction. The focus is on effective coordination, oversight, and internal ownership of compliance activities. The ideal candidate combines strong tax and compliance knowledge with operational execution skills, business partnership capabilities, and experience supporting multi-jurisdiction organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is located in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tax Compliance &amp;amp; Governance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and oversee U.S. federal, state, and local tax compliance activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage sales and use tax compliance, registrations, filings, and reporting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee tax compliance activities for the company&#39;s Canadian subsidiary in coordination with external advisors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage indirect tax compliance, including VAT, GST, HST, PST, and similar international tax obligations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate tax provision support and annual tax filings with external tax firms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor nexus exposure and compliance obligations across all jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage tax notices, audits, inquiries, and regulatory examinations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain tax compliance calendars and governance processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International Expansion Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Accounting leadership to support the company&#39;s international expansion strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
